Definition: any effect that seems to be a consequence of administering a placebo
Example: the change is usually beneficial and is assumed result from the person's faith in the treatment or preconceptions about what the experimental drug was supposed to do; pharmacologists were the first to talk about placebo effects but now the idea has been generalized to many situations having nothing to do with drugs
Synonyms: consequence, any, effect, that, seems, to, be, a, of, administering, placebo, the, change, is, usually, beneficial, and, assumed, result, from, person, s, faith, in, treatment, or, preconceptions, about, what, experimental, drug, was, supposed, do, pharmacologists, were, first, talk, effects, but, now, idea, has, been, generalized, many, situations, having, nothing, with, drugs
Category: noun.phenomenon
